WEBVTT

00:05.120 --> 00:06.370
Oh, bollocks!

00:06.454 --> 00:07.788
Dad, what's going on?

00:07.839 --> 00:09.206
Beans on toast, love.

00:09.291 --> 00:10.591
At 4 A.M.?

00:10.658 --> 00:12.843
Best time of day.

00:14.379 --> 00:16.680
Not bad on the beans,

00:16.765 --> 00:18.933
but more like
beans on crisp.

00:19.000 --> 00:22.186
Yeah. Well, I got a little
distracted, didn't I?

00:22.270 --> 00:26.157
A video of golden eagles
dragging goats off a mountain.

00:26.241 --> 00:27.408
It's brilliant.

00:27.459 --> 00:30.895
Only happens in this
one little tiny part of Spain.

00:30.962 --> 00:33.998
How's the book coming along?

00:34.082 --> 00:37.251
Let's have another whack
at the toast, then, shall we?

00:37.302 --> 00:40.154
Have you even--
have you even tried writing anything?

00:40.222 --> 00:42.973
Just a sentence,
any sentence.

00:43.058 --> 00:45.092
That's what I do when
I can't write a paper.

00:45.143 --> 00:48.012
You can go back to bed
now, love, if you want.

00:48.096 --> 00:51.015
"Happy families
are all alike.

00:51.082 --> 00:52.733
However, every
unhappy family--"

00:52.800 --> 00:54.235
bored.

00:55.487 --> 00:57.938
No, it's very Russian.

00:57.989 --> 00:59.607
You think you can do better?

01:07.999 --> 01:09.700
"Let there be Lightman."

01:11.152 --> 01:12.870
Hire a ghost writer.

01:12.954 --> 01:14.371
Good night, love.

01:16.000 --> 01:22.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:29.387 --> 01:31.372
Take them away.
Don't need 'em.

01:31.439 --> 01:34.191
All the research
I need is in here.

01:37.011 --> 01:38.729
Perfect. Deaf as a post.

01:38.813 --> 01:39.947
It's just deaf.

01:40.014 --> 01:41.715
No post.

01:45.320 --> 01:47.321
Follow me.

01:47.372 --> 01:49.856
Is Loker in?

01:49.908 --> 01:53.627
Yeah, he's somewhere.
He should be back in a minute.

01:56.831 --> 01:58.532
Sit.

02:01.869 --> 02:03.971
Stay.

02:04.038 --> 02:05.639
The red dot test.

02:05.707 --> 02:07.374
Watch.

02:12.213 --> 02:13.430
Oi!

02:13.515 --> 02:15.683
You sent Mutt and Jeff
to spy on me, didn't you? Hey?

02:15.734 --> 02:18.619
Cal Lightman,
Candice McCallister.

02:18.687 --> 02:19.937
Oh, so you don't deny that?

02:20.021 --> 02:22.573
Sarah and Charles
are here to help you, Cal.

02:22.657 --> 02:23.741
Do you two
need a minute?

02:23.825 --> 02:27.194
You know, I am having
a hard time

02:27.245 --> 02:29.113
writing this book.
Same thing happened on the first one.

02:29.197 --> 02:31.999
You know, the one
that this whole place is built on.

02:32.066 --> 02:36.036
Dr. Lightman, may I say
what a huge fan I am of that book.

02:37.572 --> 02:39.456
Is it Candice with an "i"
or Candace with an "a"?

02:39.541 --> 02:41.675
'Cause Candace with an "a"
I find to be far more classy.

02:41.743 --> 02:43.260
You know what I mean?

02:43.345 --> 02:44.878
We're running late.

02:44.929 --> 02:45.879
What can I do for you?

02:45.930 --> 02:48.265
Um, I thought you said
Dr. Lightman was--

02:48.350 --> 02:50.684
busy. That's exactly
what I said.

02:50.752 --> 02:53.053
Goodbye, Cal.

02:59.060 --> 03:01.595
Oi!

03:01.646 --> 03:03.947
Come in here.
Make yourself useful.

03:04.032 --> 03:05.282
With your book?

03:05.367 --> 03:07.234
What book?

03:07.285 --> 03:09.653
I need to see
Foster's calendar.

03:09.738 --> 03:11.905
You mean hack into
her computer.

03:11.956 --> 03:13.273
Your words, not mine.

03:13.325 --> 03:14.775
Dr. Lightman, I can't
just hack into her--

03:14.826 --> 03:15.876
or you're fired.

03:15.943 --> 03:18.379
Watch my fingers.

03:22.650 --> 03:24.752
It wasn't that hard,
was it?

03:27.255 --> 03:28.472
On your way, then.

03:33.561 --> 03:34.645
Wh--

03:34.729 --> 03:36.497
what--

03:36.564 --> 03:39.483
did--did you do this?

03:39.567 --> 03:41.318
Hey. This is my desk.

03:41.403 --> 03:42.803
I can't hear you.

03:42.854 --> 03:45.856
The red dot test.
He's got you doing the red dot test?

03:45.940 --> 03:48.192
Can you leave me alone now?

03:48.259 --> 03:49.193
Excuse me?

03:49.277 --> 03:51.478
I need to focus.

03:53.331 --> 03:55.199
No, don't worry about me.

03:55.283 --> 03:57.451
I didn't want anything
from the coffee cart.

04:26.698 --> 04:29.316
1, 2, 3, 4.

04:29.367 --> 04:32.536
1, 2, 3, 4...

04:45.199 --> 04:46.717
Oh, Megan!

04:46.801 --> 04:48.335
Your dress!

04:49.421 --> 04:50.721
It's all right, mom.

04:50.805 --> 04:52.723
You can't see it
anywhere. Relax.

04:58.480 --> 04:59.847
Help you, sir?

04:59.898 --> 05:00.898
You lost?

05:00.982 --> 05:03.066
Contestants and parents
only here.

05:04.218 --> 05:06.153
I must have wandered
through the wrong door.

05:06.220 --> 05:07.855
Well, how about you
wander back out again?

05:07.906 --> 05:10.741
Dad, you made my braid
crooked.

05:10.825 --> 05:14.194
I'd jump right
on that if I were you.

05:15.530 --> 05:17.831
How many time have I
told you, Megan,

05:17.899 --> 05:20.617
food is not your friend?

05:27.125 --> 05:28.542
I'm calling security.

05:28.593 --> 05:30.494
I work with the pageant.

05:30.562 --> 05:31.795
Yeah? Doing what?

05:31.880 --> 05:33.096
This and that.

05:33.181 --> 05:34.548
Yeah, thought so.
You're out of here.

05:34.599 --> 05:36.717
Wouldn't you rather
be a soccer mum?

05:36.768 --> 05:39.353
Drs. Foster and Lightman
are here to vet our finalists,

05:39.420 --> 05:42.606
to make sure we are
plastic surgery and drug-free.

05:42.690 --> 05:45.091
Lucky for you

05:45.143 --> 05:47.394
I got writer's block.

05:47.445 --> 05:48.779
So you got into my calendar.
Good for you.

05:48.863 --> 05:50.230
But I've got this covered, Cal.

05:50.281 --> 05:53.317
Who's the favorite

05:53.401 --> 05:55.118
in this little
Freak Show, then?

05:55.203 --> 05:56.320
Freak Show?

05:56.404 --> 05:58.038
And you wonder why
I kept you out of this.

05:58.105 --> 05:59.490
What about you?

05:59.574 --> 06:01.124
Eh?

06:01.209 --> 06:02.626
You the favorite?

06:02.710 --> 06:05.879
She is one, yes,
but nothing is certain.

06:08.049 --> 06:11.051
Well, one thing's
for certain.

06:11.118 --> 06:14.454
It's all gonna go
horribly wrong for someone.

06:14.464 --> 06:18.364
<font color=#FFFF00>♪ Lie to Me 3x02 ♪ </font>
<font color=#00FFFF>The Royal We </font>
<font color=#FF7F00>Brand New Day</font> by Ryan Star

06:18.393 --> 06:21.728
♪ dream,
send me a sign ♪

06:21.796 --> 06:24.348
♪ turn back the clock ♪

06:24.432 --> 06:26.683
♪ give me some time ♪

06:26.768 --> 06:29.486
♪ I need to break out ♪

06:29.571 --> 06:31.555
♪ make a new name ♪

06:31.623 --> 06:34.525
♪ let's open our eyes ♪

06:34.609 --> 06:41.131
♪ to the brand-new day ♪

